facts.value:
Frank LaMar Watkins, 79, of Mesa, a retired letter carrier, died 
Feb. 28, 1998. He was born in Hebe City, Utah. Survivors include his wife, Alicegean; daughters, Louise Burnlam, Coleen Taylor, Betty Reed, Karen Hyles; sons, Sheria Mead and Karen Hyles; sons,  F. LaMar, Randy, Robert and Keith; sister, Rhea Swain and Margene Cobbly; brother, Jack; 33 grand-children; and 16 great-grandchildren. Visitation: 6 to 8 p.m. Friday, Mezona Ward Building, 1054 W. 2nd Place, Mesa. Services: 10 a.rn. Saturday, at the church. Meldrum Mortuary.
